HEADWORD: Ephesian
<hw>E*phe"sian</hw> <pr>(?; 106)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Ephesius</ets>: cf. F. <ets>⟦eacute⟧ph⟦eacute⟧sien</ets>.]</ety>
<def>Of or pertaining to <etsep>Ephesus</etsep>, an ancient city of
Ionia, in Asia Minor.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ephesian</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ephesian
<hw>E*phe"sian</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A native of
Ephesus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A jolly companion; a roisterer.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ephialtes</ent>⟦br⟧
